Train Movement Logic

Your trains are NOT real GPS—they are computed positions

🔹 How movement works
station A → station B → station C

You calculate:

progress = elapsed_time / travel_time

Then:

lat = lat1 + (lat2 - lat1) * progress
lng = lng1 + (lng2 - lng1) * progress

👉 This is called linear interpolation

